The Agriculture Department has announced a total shutdown on the movement of livestock in parts of KwaZulu-Natal. eNCA reporter Lethiwe Mdluli has more on this. Courtesy of #DStv403  DURBAN - The Agriculture Department has announced a total shutdown on the movement of livestock in parts of KwaZulu-Natal in an effort to stop the spread of Foot and Mouth Disease. READ:Â Brucellosis outbreak: Rural KZN farmers losing cattle The most affected areas include UMkhanyakude, King Cetshwayo, and the Zululand Districts. KZN Agriculture and Rural Development MEC Bongiwe Sithole-Moloi will be meeting with affected farmers.